Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing, his probation having been revoked effective 02-16-18.   
Count 3 - Possess Methamphetamine - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of three and one-half (3 1/2) years.   Eighteen (18) months initial confinement, followed by twenty-four (24) months extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:  
1) Have no contact with Craig Holtz; 
2) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
3) AODA assessment and follow through; 
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination unless medically excused; 
6) Submit DNA sample; 
7) Pay costs of action; 
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.   
Count 5 - PTC Manufacture Methamphetamine - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of four (4) years.   Twenty-four (24) months initial confinement, followed by twenty-four (24) months extended supervision concurrent with count 3.   Conditions of extended supervision are the same.   
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Substance Abuse Program.  
Defendant is given credit for 695 days on count 3 and 424 days on count 5.   
